description.narrative: UNICEF Pacific continued to increase knowledge of the risk of poor WASH practices in several PICTs, with a particular focus on Solomon Islands. As a result, fewer people are now practicing open defecation in the country, with 50 more communities in Malaita Province declared ODF in 2019. Other activities, including national handwashing campaigns, were carried out in Fiji, Kiribati, FSM, Solomon Islands and Vanuatu. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
